721112f-a.text:
1895 to 1885 (left to right) Lexington Avenue, at, adjoining and south of the S. E. corner of East 118th Street, showing a row of structures included in the Mandel Estate auction sale on January 24, 1917. At the right margin appears a partial view of a doublefront building that stands on the spot where Harlem Road joined the Eastern Post Road. At the left is a three story frame house bearing No. 152 E. 118th St.
1917
